<h4>JEWELS</h4>
<p>White</p>
<p>Yellow</p>
<p>Tiger Eye</p>
<p>Rose</p>
<p>Summer-sky</p>
<p>Purple Dusk</p>
<p>Opal*</p>
<p>Green</p>
<p>Sapphire</p>
<p>Red</p>
<p>Gray</p>
<p>Ebon-gray</p>

<p>Black</p>
<p>*Opal is the dividing line between lighter and darker Jewels because it can be either.</p>
<p>When making the Offering to the Darkness, a person can descend a maximum of three ranks from his/her Birthright Jewel.</p>
<p>Example: Birthright White could descend to Rose.</p>
</div><div>

<h4>BLOOD HIERARCHY/CASTES</h4>
<p>Males:</p>
<p>landen&hellip;non-Blood of any race</p>
<p>Blood male&hellip;a general term for all males of the Blood; also refers to any</p>
<p>Blood male who doesn't wear Jewels Warlord&hellip;a Jeweled male equal in status to a witch Prince&hellip;a Jeweled male equal in status to a Priestess or a Healer Warlord Prince&hellip;a dangerous, extremely aggressive Jeweled male; in status, slightly lower than a Queen</p>
</div><div>

<p>Females:</p>
<p>landen&hellip;non-Blood of any race</p>
<p>Blood female&hellip;a general term for all females of the Blood; mostly refers to any Blood female who doesn't wear Jewels</p>
<p>witch&hellip;a Blood female who wears Jewels but isn't one of the other hierarchical levels; also refers to any Jeweled female</p>
<p>Healer&hellip;a witch who heals physical wounds and illnesses; equal in status to a Priestess and a Prince</p>
<p>Priestess&hellip;a witch who cares for altars, Sanctuaries and Dark Altars; witnesses handfasts and marriages; performs offerings; equal in status to a Healer and a Prince</p>
<p>Black Widow&hellip;a witch who heals the mind; weaves the tangled webs of dreams and visions; is trained in illusions and poisons</p>
<p>Queen&hellip;a witch who rules the Blood; is considered to be the land's heart and the Blood's moral center; as such, she is the focal point of their society</p>
</div><div>

